node.text: The internet made me realize me don’t like women. Their comments on women’s pages are wild!! They hate us!!
@shrinkiesxwife yes. 💯

The Biggest Plot Twist About Men No One Talks About… 🤯

Ever wondered why some men seem to want women but don’t actually like them? Turns out, the way boys are raised plays a huge role. Society doesn’t teach them how to be men, it just teaches them not to be like women. 💡

❌ "Don't cry, be a man."
❌ "Don't be weak, be a man."
❌ "Don't like that, it's for girls."

And the weapon of choice? Shame.
They’re taught that being feminine is the worst thing ever. But at the same time, their status is measured by their ability to attract women. See the contradiction? 🧐

No wonder so many women feel unseen, unheard, and undervalued. Maybe it's time to start asking: Do they truly like women, or just what women can do for them?

Let’s talk. 👇✨

So men in this comment section listened to this and said 'yeah but girls don't like each other either'. There are no real men left! We are doomed!! Maybe if a man had said it they would have listened.......😢
@kalistablair you're raising a new breed of young men, thank you🙏🏼
@kalistablair you should be proud 🥹 smart boy. We can help stop the cycle of shaming boys for simply being a human with a full range of feelings.
@kalistablair wow, props to your son and you being willing to dissect that with him

My 7yo boy was watching Diary of a Wimpy Kid that came out in 2010. The coach yelled to the boys only class to "get up ladies, quit knitting" (or something like that). He looked at me with such a confused look, and asked "why is it a bad thing to be knitting and why does he think callling them ladies is an insult?" This was the first time we have ever encountered this together, or even talked about it. He came to the conclusion that the coach was trying to insult the boys on his own. I am so proud of him.

The amount of men here thinking this is a misandrist take is insane…
In fact, this causes problems to men too and acknowledging it would be great for everybody.
This is definitely a factor in men loneliness, how can you find a partner of you don’t know how to love them?
How can you have a healthy relationship with a woman or a healthy celibate life if you’re both craving for women but at the same time looking down on them?
And how do you expect women to give you a chance or to stay if you see them as the worst thing you could be yourself?
@macjnjoku I thought everyone had the right to express themselves and everyone should be held to the same standards. Because women want to be seen as equals not soft delicate objects.
@bigbydesign68 You didn’t read that right. I’m talking about when men rape children if the woman kills the rapist she’ll go to prison. However, if for the father does it he’ll get found not guilty.

@shrinkiesxwife Women tend use character assination and weaponize the police against men  with no.jail time.or.accountability . Those rarely face jail time unless they had the option to leave and contact the police.

Is funny how you associate being a man with not liking women.  The world is a cold place for men because a man that has out burst or unfavorable opinions is seen as a threat. The treatment of a single dad and a single mom is two different things. Women face kess jail time than men even when they commit similar crimes.
@build_junkie lmao buddy I’ve got plenty reason. Women are evil, selfish creatures who are capable of committing heinous acts without a second thought.
@build_junkie thank you
@pprincessoni Yea right

Sorry, dudes, but my girl here is 100% spot on. I've actually kinda studied bullying in general & the outright hatefulness towards women. I was actually quite shocked at not just the amount, but how openly hateful a large amount of men are with literally zero reason behind it. Come on guys we can do better than this.
You’re joking, right? India is one of the worst places to be a woman. And not only that, but the cast system is horrible as well. Lack of any consideration towards fellow humans… is fully on.

India? Where women are raped constantly ??? I think India should sit this one out  especially in a country where shame leads men to unalive women who they think rebuff them. Leave the chat India!. Log off

@realcharmi2023 you drank the kool-aid too. All over the Indian diaspora, domestic violence and SA against women is HIGH, so you lot are clearly lost in the sauce. Indian men seem to use brute force against women and children

Sure if you base masculinity entirely on western ideas. But, in an Indian perspective, masculinity is not just defined by brute force, it includes discipline, sacrifice, righteousness, truthfulness. Around the world ancient cultures described about warrior poets, people who were warriors and appreciated the arts. The Euro centric idea of masculinity sees pursuit of the arts and poetry as girlie, while most of the rest of the world doesn't.

This is not really the case in the US. Girls are now encouraged to be tough, play sports, get messy, be a leader, etc. so both girls and boys are taught to look down on feminine traits. It’s something we have to consciously unlearn. Women proudly say they are not like other girls, one of the guys, etc.

I come from a country that does this. The difference for me is that this don't be the opposite sex is done to men by deep shame, for women it's not as intense unless it's to control their bodies or modest police/purity culture. You're not savagely mocked as a girl if you play roughly, the same way a boy who acts like a girl is.

Not sure how it’s in the US, but I grew up in a traditional patriarchal country and girls were raised in a similar way: you don’t want to be like boys: “don’t be dirty and messy… like boys”, “don’t be aggressive… like boys”. Also it’s kind of subtly suggested that being too “tough” and “work too hard physically” is also a manly thing that’s making you “less of a woman”. And you really want to be a woman.
@debrinacrivelli a good man will strengthen a ladies sounds like you have a good man :)

@sonshine_stables I do see what you mean however the don’t think this is about ‘blaming’ others. if you blame others you already see the issue. The problem is when you are not aware or refuse to work on yourself

Uuummm wwrrooonngggg  so wrong. Our beautiful wives ate also our best friends. You are deflecting your personal experiences on others.

This is so real and so disturbing…

I had no father figure and never hung out with groups of guys. My strongest and best friendships have always been girls and women.

I tell people often that men want women but not the emotions that come with us, all while telling us to not be so masculine.. You can’t hd r it both ways

@frauvonwell How are they embarrassing themselves?  Pretend I accuse you of being a space alien sent here to spy on us. You reply, “Not at all!” I say, “Prove it.” The problem is, you can’t. What is going on here isn’t science, or grounded in science. It’s rhetoric designed to bait, to entrap, and to further divide. And it’s revolting. No human is capable of proving their innocence with respect to such ludicrous claims about their own existential states. Try it out for yourself and see how it goes. You can’t accuse someone of having a negative internal state and then ask them to prove they don’t have that state. Think about it. Moreover, if it’s wrong when guys do this to women (and it is), it’s exactly as wrong to go the other direction. Let’s all give a little grace and imagine that the other side is actually human, and not filled with poison and treachery. Cheers.
Thank you, this is very interesting! And the men in the comments crying "wrong!" without presenting any arguments whatsoever are just embarrassing themselves.
